## Widget Architecture

### Standard Widget Structure

All widgets follow this base structure:

```tsx
<div className="p-4 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-card shadow-card">
  <div className="space-y-4">
    {/* Section 1: Header (optional) */}
    <section>
      <h3 className="text-sm font-semibold text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary mb-2">
        Widget Title (3)  {/* Count badge if applicable */}
      </h3>
      {/* Content */}
    </section>

    {/* Section 2: List/Grid (optional) */}
    <section>
      <ul className="space-y-3">
        <li>Item 1</li>
        <li>Item 2</li>
        <li>Item 3</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    {/* Section 3: Action Button (last element) */}
    <button className="w-full px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue-hover text-white font-medium transition-colors">
      Primary Action
    </button>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Key Principles:**
1. **Container:** `p-4` padding (16px) for all widgets
2. **Content wrapper:** `space-y-4` (16px between sections)
3. **List items:** `space-y-3` (12px between items)
4. **Action button:** Last element (no gap beneath)

