## Spacing Standards

### Internal Padding

**Standard:** `p-4` (16px) for ALL widgets

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<div className="p-4 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark">
  {/* Content */}
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect
<div className="p-3">  {/* Too small */}
<div className="p-6">  {/* Too large */}
```

**Rationale:** Consistent padding creates visual harmony across all widgets.

---

### Content Section Spacing

**Standard:** `space-y-4` (16px) between content sections

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<div className="space-y-4">
  <section>Header</section>
  <section>List</section>
  <button>Action</button>
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect
<div className="space-y-2">  {/* Too tight */}
<div className="space-y-6">  {/* Too loose */}
```

**Rationale:** 16px provides clear visual separation without wasting space.

---

### List Item Spacing

**Standard:** `space-y-3` (12px) between list items

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<ul className="space-y-3">
  <li>Task 1</li>
  <li>Task 2</li>
  <li>Task 3</li>
</ul>

// ❌ Incorrect
<ul className="space-y-2">  {/* Too tight */}
<ul className="space-y-4">  {/* Too loose (same as sections) */}
```

**Rationale:** 12px is tighter than section spacing to show items are related.

---

### No Bottom Gap

**Critical:** Do NOT add extra spacing beneath the last element (action button).

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - No extra spacing
<div className="space-y-4">
  <section>Content</section>
  <button>Action</button>  {/* Last element, no gap after */}
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect - Extra bottom gap
<div className="space-y-4">
  <section>Content</section>
  <button>Action</button>
  <div className="mb-4"></div>  {/* Creates "big gap beneath buttons" */}
</div>
```

**Rationale:** Extra bottom spacing creates a "big gap" that looks unfinished.

