## Button Standards

### Primary Action Button

**Standard:** Full-width button at bottom of widget

```tsx
<button className="w-full px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue-hover text-white font-medium transition-colors">
  View All Tasks
</button>
```

**Required Classes:**
- `w-full` - Full width (stretches to container)
- `px-4 py-2` - Horizontal 16px, vertical 8px padding (40px height)
- `rounded-lg` - 8px border radius
- `bg-accent-{color}` - Accent color (blue/magenta/cyan)
- `hover:bg-accent-{color}-hover` - Hover state
- `text-white` - White text
- `font-medium` - 500 font weight
- `transition-colors` - Smooth hover transition

**Result:** Uniform button height (40px) across ALL widgets

---

### Secondary Action Button (Optional)

If widget needs multiple actions:

```tsx
<div className="flex gap-2">
  <button className="flex-1 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue-hover text-white font-medium transition-colors">
    Action 1
  </button>
  <button className="flex-1 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-surface-light-elevated dark:bg-surface-dark-elevated hover:bg-surface-light dark:hover:bg-surface-dark text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary font-medium transition-colors border border-border-light dark:border-border-dark">
    Action 2
  </button>
</div>
```

**Key:** Use `flex-1` instead of `w-full` + `gap-2` (8px) between buttons

---

### Button Size Comparison

**Before (Non-uniform):**
```tsx
// Widget 1
<button className="w-full px-3 py-1.5">  {/* 32px height */}

// Widget 2
<button className="w-full px-4 py-2.5">  {/* 44px height */}

// Widget 3
<button className="w-full px-4 py-2">  {/* 40px height */}
```

**Result:** Buttons different heights - visually inconsistent

---

**After (Uniform):**
```tsx
// ALL widgets
<button className="w-full px-4 py-2">  {/* ALWAYS 40px height */}
```

**Result:** All buttons same height - visually consistent ✅

