## Color Usage

### Accent Colors for Distinct Widgets

Use different accent colors to visually distinguish widget types:

| Widget Type | Accent Color | Hex | Use Case |
|-------------|--------------|-----|----------|
| Tasks | `accent-blue` | `#3b82f6` | Task-related widgets |
| Events | `accent-magenta` | `#ec4899` | Calendar/event widgets |
| Notes | `accent-cyan` | `#06b6d4` | Note-taking widgets |

**Example:**
```tsx
// Tasks Widget
<button className="... bg-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue-hover">
  View All Tasks
</button>

// Events Widget
<button className="... bg-accent-magenta hover:bg-accent-magenta-hover">
  View All Events
</button>

// Notes Widget
<button className="... bg-accent-cyan hover:bg-accent-cyan-hover">
  View All Notes
</button>
```

**Rationale:** Distinct colors help users quickly identify widget type at a glance.

---

### Background Colors

Use semantic surface colors for widget backgrounds:

```tsx
<div className="bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark">
  {/* Light mode: white (#FFFFFF) */}
  {/* Dark mode: black (#000000) */}
</div>

<div className="bg-surface-light-elevated dark:bg-surface-dark-elevated">
  {/* Light mode: light gray (#F8F9FA) */}
  {/* Dark mode: dark gray (#1A1A1A) */}
</div>
```

**Standard:** Use `surface-light` / `surface-dark` for widget backgrounds.

