## Testing Checklist

Before shipping a widget, verify:

### Visual Standards
- [ ] Widget padding is `p-4` (16px)
- [ ] Content sections use `space-y-4` (16px)
- [ ] List items use `space-y-3` (12px)
- [ ] Action button is `w-full px-4 py-2` (40px height)
- [ ] No extra spacing beneath action button
- [ ] Drag handle in upper-right corner (if applicable)
- [ ] Accent color matches widget type (blue/magenta/cyan)

### Responsive Design
- [ ] Works on mobile (375px)
- [ ] Works on tablet (768px)
- [ ] Works on desktop (1920px)
- [ ] Button text doesn't wrap on mobile
- [ ] Content doesn't overflow widget

### Dark Mode
- [ ] All text readable in dark mode
- [ ] Background colors use semantic tokens
- [ ] Button hover states work in dark mode
- [ ] No hardcoded light/dark colors

### Accessibility
- [ ] Button has accessible label
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Focus states visible
- [ ] Screen reader announces widget correctly

### Code Quality
- [ ] Uses spacing standards from `docs/technical/spacing-standards.md`
- [ ] Uses semantic color tokens from `src/index.css`
- [ ] No hardcoded spacing values (no `p-[14px]`, use `p-4`)
- [ ] TypeScript types defined for all props
- [ ] Component exported from index file

